title: Willard Frederic Elms Art Institute by the Elevated Lines Poster
description:
Poster developed from Willard Frederic Elms’ Art Institute by the Elevated Lines, 1924, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Willard Elms was an art teacher at the Art Institute of Chicago, who also received his art education there. He owned his own studio in Chicago with his main client being the Sears Roebuck catalog. He also was an announcer for WGN radio. He then moved to Arizona working as a poster and fashion artist.

  • Dimensions: 18 x 24 in.
  • Material: Premium Cardstock
